    {
        "content": "<p>good point, looking <a href=\"https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/master/arch/riscv/kernel/sys_riscv.c#L59-L61\">at the syscall itself</a> it looks like EPERM isn't ever returned</p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/master/arch/riscv/kernel/sys_riscv.c#L59-L61\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/3fc392e426162a1981f93e31aee559513a6008ab/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f313339326135346437656531306231323361353363646365623366333932376430326339656431326137313263346431643664366662356261316636633936372f746f7276616c64732f6c696e7578&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/master/arch/riscv/kernel/sys_riscv.c#L59-L61\" title=\"linux/arch/riscv/kernel/sys_riscv.c at master · torvalds/linux\">linux/arch/riscv/kernel/sys_riscv.c at master · torvalds/linux</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">Linux kernel source tree. Contribute to torvalds/linux development by creating an account on GitHub.</div></div></div>",
